{
  "_README": [
    "Empirical title-format fixture for the end-detection window probe.",
    "",
    "Each entry pins one (bundle_id, state) pair to the literal window",
    "titles AX returned for the meeting app in that state, plus the",
    "expected recognizer outcome (`recognize` / `reject`).",
    "",
    "How to add real captures (Roadmap P1.1):",
    "  1. Open the app, drive it into the named state.",
    "  2. With Accessibility permission granted to a script, dump",
    "     `kAXWindowsAttribute -> kAXTitleAttribute` for that PID.",
    "  3. Drop the captured title list into a new entry below, set",
    "     `expected` based on whether a meeting is in progress, and",
    "     re-run `WindowRecognizerFixtureTests`.",
    "",
    "The current entries are seeded from `WindowRecognizerTests` and",
    "represent expected formats, not yet field-verified captures.",
    "Once Heorhii captures real titles, replace `seeded: true` with",
    "`seeded: false` for that entry."
  ],
  "entries": [
    {
      "bundle_id": "us.zoom.xos",
      "state": "in_call_with_topic",
      "expected": "recognize",
      "seeded": true,
      "titles": ["Daily standup | Zoom Meeting"]
    },
    {
      "bundle_id": "us.zoom.xos",
      "state": "in_call_no_topic",
      "expected": "recognize",
      "seeded": true,
      "titles": ["Zoom Meeting"]
    },
    {
      "bundle_id": "us.zoom.xos",
      "state": "idle_launcher",
      "expected": "reject",
      "seeded": true,
      "titles": ["Zoom"]
    },
    {
